1 -  Define a Thread class
		- Either subclass a Thread or
		- Implement an interface named Runnable
2 - Override a method named run() and have this method do what you want to do
3 - Create the object of this Thread
	- If you define a subclass of Thread - create an Object
	- If you implement Runnable - create an object of Runnable and create a Thread on top of Runnable
4 - Invoke a method named start() on the above Object